OL,6,FMiss Boothby-O'Neill had suffered with
OL,7,FME for a decade before she died at
OL,8,Fhome in Exeter in October 2021 from
OL,9,Fsevere malnutrition.
OL,11,FAn inquest heard she had been admitted
OL,12,Fto the Royal Devon and Exeter Hospital
OL,13,Fthree times that year for treatment
OL,14,Ffor malnutrition.
OL,16,FThe 10-day hearing focused on the
OL,17,Ffinal few months of her life, by which
OL,18,Ftime she was confined to bed, unable
OL,19,Fto chew food and had difficulty
OL,20,Fdrinking because she was not able to
OL,21,Fsit up.
